<title>JAPAN: Japan's THK Co names new president.</title>
<headline>Japan's THK Co names new president.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-01-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>THK Co Ltd said on Monday that Hiroshi Teramachi had stepped down as its president and had been replaced by his son Akihiro Teramachi, who formerly held the post of vice president.</p>
<p>The announcement was made after the Tokyo stock market closed.</p>
<p>Earlier, shares in the leading maker of rolling linear motion-guide systems closed at 1,160 yen compared with Friday's finish at 1,280 yen.</p>
<p>THK said the personnel change was designed to promote younger management at the company.</p>
